課程概述 Course Description
       本科目藉由文獻閱讀及討論，激發學生能敏覺健康照護的倫理議題，並促使學生思辨生命倫理之基本哲學理論與原則、醫病關係法則、邏輯、價值觀、及各類倫理兩難困境，增進反省、批判性思考、倫理抉擇及行為擇善的能力。 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
enhance students’ sensitivity toward ethical issues in healthcare professionmotivate the students to debate the philosophical-based theoryimprove their self-awareness, critical thinkingdevelop the capability to inspect and analyze ethical issuesdetermine the appropriate actions for ethical decision 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Course Introduction2Relationship ethics and Debate3Fundamental Knowledge of Bioethics4Moral and Ethics (Joint class)5My values of moral and life6International Week7Ethics and Cultural Diversity (Joint class)8Clinical/Research Ethic Issues–Informed consent9Clinical Ethic Issues–Care of Maternal and Child patients10Clinical Ethic Issues–Care of Psychiatric/community patients(Joint class)11Clinical Ethic Issues–Care of Geriatric patients12Clinical Ethic Issues–End of Life Care13Clinical Ethic Issues–Clinical case analysis14Research Ethics and Participants Protection15Academic Integrity and Ethics16Ethical Issues/Student report (I)17Ethical Issues/Student report(II)18Course Evaluation 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


